.TH _printf 3 "April 2026" "1.0" "_printf manual"

.SH NAME
        _printf \- formatted output conversion

.SH SYNOPSIS
        .B #include "main.h"
        .PP
        .B int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
        The _printf function produces output according to a format string.

It supports the following conversion specifier:
.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a string.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a percent sign.
.TP
.B %d
Prints an integer.
.TP
.B %i
Prints an integer.

.SH RETURN VALUE
         Returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte).
         If an error occurs, -1 is returned.

.SH EXAMPLES
        _printf("Hello %s\n", "Ali");
        _printf("Number: %d\n", 123);

